<subSubSection pageId="297" pageNumber="298" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="297" pageNumber="298">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="297" pageNumber="298">
This European species is adventive in North America where it is known only from the Vancouver area in southwestern British Columbia (Bousquet 1997a: 94, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bousquet" authorityYear="1997" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dyschirius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="297" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glomerosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="297" pageNumber="298">Dyschirius glomerosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The first inventoried specimen collected on this continent was found in 1978.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
